name: Mount Field

trails_config.name: Avalon & A–Z Loop
trails_config.description: From Crawford Depot, climb the Avalon Trail steeply past sparkling Cascade Brook to the spur for Mt Avalon’s viewpoint, then continue to Mount Field’s summit. Return via the A–Z Trail through quiet boreal forest. This loop provides a mix of a great mid-hike view from Avalon and the high elevation spruce ambiance of Field’s broad summit (where gray jays often greet hikers).

current_conditions.ai_summary: Experience the beauty of New Hampshire on Mount Field. At 4340 feet, this summit commands impressive views of the surrounding wilderness.
risk_factors: Check local trail conditions before departing.
Start early to avoid afternoon storms.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4340 feet, Mount Field is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its approachable and scenic terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Avalon & A–Z Loop**, a **6.4 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Mount Avalon**, which is just 0.6 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
